heaviest_rainfall.status: The largest amount of rain ever recorded is on 04 January 2025 when 36.8mm fell at a maximum rate of 4.6mm per hour over the 37.2 hour event.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today, the rain fell at an intense rate peaking at 16.2mm per hour, one of the heaviest downpours recorded and ranked 4th from our records.  The precipitation lasted 6.9 hours and dumped 9.36mm in total.  27.0mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.

longest_rain.status: Rain fell for 37.2 hours on 04 January 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 36.8mm with a maximum intensity of 4.6mm per hour.

summary.description:
Today, cooler for the feels like temperature (down 2.5°C), outside temperature (down 2.3°C), and inside temperature (down 1.8°C) and more moisture-laden outside humidity (up 8%).

The past week and month had observable variation in cloud levels (up 1247 m), light levels (up 7458 lux), and rainfall (down 0.5 mm) when compared to today.
